      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <!-- Risks -->
      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Risks and Transparency</span><span class="lang-zh">風險同透明度</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The decentralization claims deserve scrutiny. The validator set is only 21, with the team controlling the majority. The bridge is controlled by 4 team addresses. In March 2025, a trader manipulated the JELLY token price; the team responded by overriding the oracle and force-liquidating positions. Arthur Hayes commented: "stop pretending Hyperliquid is decentralized."</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">去中心化嘅聲稱值得審視。驗證者集合只有21個，團隊控制大多數。Bridge由4個團隊地址控制。2025年3月，一個trader操縱JELLY代幣價格；團隊override oracle定價並強制清算倉位。Arthur Hayes評論：「唔好再扮Hyperliquid係去中心化。」</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Risk factors: smart contract exploits on bridge or matching engine, oracle manipulation (proven by JELLY incident), unilateral team intervention, no regulatory oversight (not an SFC-licensed VATP), no KYC, no deposit protection, no recourse. HIP-3 deployers control oracles and margin rules for their markets — you trust the deployer, not just Hyperliquid core. Size positions accordingly.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">風險因素：bridge或matching engine嘅智能合約漏洞、預言機操縱（JELLY事件已證明）、團隊單方面干預、無監管監督（唔係SFC持牌VATP）、無KYC、無存款保障、無追索權。HIP-3 deployers控制自己市場嘅oracle同margin rules — 你唔單止信Hyperliquid core，仲要信deployer。相應調整倉位規模。</span>
      </p>

